 new and original analysis of landholding in the village, which depicts the land market in unprecedented detail, and explores the changing significance of landownership for ordinary people.It is a key work for all those interested in how English rural society changed between the sixteenth and eighteenth centuries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aAlan Macfarlane.  aEarls Colne.  aEnglish Individualism.  aEnglish rural society.  aHarlakendens.  aRalph Josselin.  aRobert Brenner.  aearly modern England.  aownership of land.  aresident gentry family.1 aFrench, H. R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoyle, R. W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoyle, Richard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779140540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847791405423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847791405/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles